I am building a turn-based 2D wrestling game called Piledriver using 
React + Vite + Phaser 3. The project is already scaffolded. 

Data files are in /src/data/:
- wrestlers.json  (5 wrestlers with attrs, physical, appearance)
- moves.json      (23 moves — offensive and defensive)
- outcomes.json   (probability table keyed by offense_id → defense_id)

Read all three files before writing any code.

Key attribute rules from wrestlers.json _schema:
- stamina = health pool (match ends at 0)
- toughness = resistance to pin kickouts and submission tapouts
- excitement = no game function yet, ignore it
- all other attrs modify move success probability per the 
  adjust_by_offense_attr / adjust_by_defense_attr fields in moves.json

Build the game engine only — no visuals yet. Create these files:

/src/engine/DataLoader.js
  - Loads and exposes wrestlers.json, moves.json, outcomes.json
  - Provides helper: getAvailableMoves(wrestler, type) that filters 
    moves by type ('Offense'|'Defense') and returns only moves the 
    wrestler meets the attribute requirements for

/src/engine/OutcomeResolver.js
  - resolveTurn(offenseMove, defenseMove, attacker, defender)
  - Looks up base probabilities from outcomes.json
  - Adjusts probabilities using attacker/defender attributes per 
    adjust_by_offense_attr and adjust_by_defense_attr
  - Rolls against final probabilities
  - Returns one of: 'success' | 'escape' | 'block' | 'reversal'
  - If reversal: also returns the reversal move id from 
    counter_move field in moves.json

/src/engine/MatchState.js
  - Tracks stamina for both wrestlers (initialized from wrestler data)
  - applyDamage(wrestlerId, amount) — reduces stamina
  - checkPin(wrestler) — rolls against toughness to determine kickout
  - checkSubmission(wrestler) — rolls against toughness to determine tapout
  - isMatchOver() — returns winner id or null

/src/engine/TurnManager.js
  - Orchestrates a single turn: 
    getOffenseMoves(wrestler) → player chooses → 
    getDefenseMoves(wrestler) → player/CPU chooses → 
    resolves outcome → applies damage → returns full turn result object
  - CPU logic: weighted random selection from available moves, 
    weighted by wrestler brains attribute

Write clean ES6 modules with JSDoc comments. No React, no Phaser — 
pure logic only. After writing each file, write a simple console 
test that exercises it so we can verify it works before moving on.